    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"5-73\">\n<h2>5-73</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 8, Section 1: Selecting Appropriate Models</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Analyzes a nonlinear recursive sequence and classifies it as neither arithmetic nor geometric.</div>\n<div class=\"contentContainerReference-body\"><div><div><div><p>Avery and Collin were trying to challenge each other with equations for sequences.  Avery wrote:</p><p><em>         $t(n+1)=(t(n))^2-1$</em><br/> <em>         $t(1)=3$</em></p><ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\"><li><p>Help Collin write the first $4$ terms of this sequence.</p></li><li><p>Is Avery’s sequence arithmetic, geometric, or some other kind of sequence?  How do you know?</p></li><li><p>Describe to Collin how he could find the $10^{th}$ term of this sequence.  You do not need to actually find the $10^{th}$ term.</p></li></ol></div></div></div></div>\n</section>",
