    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"7-78\">\n<h2>7-78</h2>\n<div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Review/Preview</span> Sorted to Unit 8, Section 1: Selecting Appropriate Models</div>\n<div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Uses data to select and fit a nonlinear model, connecting disk radius to weight through area.</div>\n<p>Each team in Ms. Zaleski’s class cut circular disks from cardboard file folders. They could cut the disks any size they chose. The weight and radius were recorded. The information is shown in the table below. Since students chose the radius, consider radius the independent variable. <a class=\"etool-link\" href=\"https://www.desmos.com/calculator/tgiyrnn9ry\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">7-78 HW eTool</a></p>\n<table>\n<tr><th>Radius (cm)</th><td>9.6</td><td>9</td><td>7.7</td><td>6.3</td><td>5.3</td><td>4.7</td><td>3.7</td><td>2.4</td><td>1.3</td></tr>\n<tr><th>Weight (g)</th><td>5.4</td><td>4.6</td><td>3.4</td><td>2.3</td><td>1.6</td><td>1.2</td><td>0.8</td><td>0.3</td><td>0.1</td></tr>\n</table>\n<ol class=\"lower-alpha\" type=\"a\">\n<li><p>Make a scatterplot for the data and sketch it onto your paper. Describe the association between weight and radius.</p></li>\n<li><p>The weight of the cardboard disk depends on its area. What kind of equation do you suggest to model this data?</p></li>\n<li><p>Model the data with a regression equation. Does the <em>y</em>-intercept of your model make sense in this context?</p></li>\n<li><p>What do you predict a 7-cm disk will weigh? Use appropriate precision in your answer.</p></li>\n</ol>\n</section>",
